I can answer some of these questions, and have clarification questions
about some of them before I relay them:

1. The funds we have in HSBC Jersey - can we transfer them to someplace
else under the same conditions?
Yes, as long as they remain outside the UK.

2. Are all investments in the UK subject to marginal tax rates (not just
bonds)?
When you ask about marginal tax rates, is this as opposed to CGT? Or
something else?

3. Are the profits in the lending deals in Jersey that are not produced in
the UK subject to marginal tax?
Will relay this question.

4. Are all profits in the Jersey account taxed at LIFO?  If not, what
countries are excepted (which countries are and which countries are not)?
LIFO applies to funds remitted to the UK, regardless of where gains
crystallised. That is, gains are taxed first, then capital can be remitted
untaxed.

5. Can the funds be transferred to another bank in the UK?
Can you please clarify which funds you are referring to? Do you mean the
capital that currently sits in Jersey?
When you say 'to *another* bank in the UK', this assumes there is already
an account in the UK, which isn't the case. Can you clarify?

6. Would a legally signed pledge that the funds will be invested only in
credit deals and bonds change the answer as to whether the funds can be
transferred to another bank or another country?
Funds can be transferred to another bank or country without incurring a tax
in the UK (unless they pass through the UK). Does that make the question
moot?

7. Finally, can  you remind me of the legal and tax implications of this
account =E2=80=93 what are the limitations, tax rates, etc.
Are you asking about the implication of a Jersey account vis-a-vis the UK?
Or tax rates in Jersey? What type of limitations are you asking about?

>

--00000000000030f72705946446fb
